name: media_png_invalid_zero_dimensions
description: |
  A deliberately invalid PNG with a valid signature and valid IHDR CRC, but
  IHDR declares both width and height as zero. PNG image dimensions are unsigned
  31-bit integers, but zero is forbidden. This should fail at IHDR validation
  before any pixel allocation or decompression work is attempted.

  This file is independently constructed for this corpus and is MIT licensed.
  PNG Suite documents an invalid 0x0 grayscale file as x00n0g01; this input is
  not copied from PNG Suite, but targets the same known-problematic class:
  https://www.libpng.org/pub/png/pngsuite.html
  https://www.w3.org/TR/png-3/#11IHDR
format: hex
decode-as: bytes
mime-type: image/png
licence: MIT
pair:
  - with: valid-minimal-rgba-1x1.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "media"
  - "image"
  - "png"
  - "invalid-png"
  - "known-problematic"
  - "png-suite-inspired"
  - "ihdr"
  - "dimensions"
---
89 50 4e 47 0d 0a 1a 0a
00 00 00 0d 49 48 44 52 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 01 00 00 00 00 13 f0 41 bf
00 00 00 00 49 45 4e 44 ae 42 60 82
